<div id="c17">
<p>&#8220;As I tried to make clear at the end, my goal in the piece was understanding what Google meant by evil so that people arguing with them could be maximally persuasive.&#8221; [do you have a quote tag?]</p>

<p>Why look at the slogan as anything more than a marketing gimmick? If their use of &#8220;evil&#8221; had an exact meaning, they&#8217;d tell us. I would think that the maximally persuasive way to argue &#8220;with them&#8221; (Google is not going to argue with you) or to the public is to appeal to shared notions of right and wrong.</p>

<p>Trying to decipher a meaning from a vague corporate slogan and then arguing it on those terms seems counterproductive.</p>

