<p>You can&#8217;t really chalk this one up as evil just because you are not aware of the potential difference between genuine and generic ink</p>

<p>I have yet to find anyone who makes provable claims for the archival permanence of third party inks</p>

<p>Have a look at independent testing by the Wilhelm Institute to learn more and while inks are expensive, the chips are there to protect us from fading prints and the manufacturer from warranty claims for which they should not be liable</p>

